verbose_text: According to these results, we note that, hydrocyanic acid levels in our samples of apricot kernels (851.04 +/- 303.28 mg/kg), obtained by the argentometric method, are slightly lower than those found in a study conducted at the Algerian University " El Tarf " and whose object was to determine the nutritional value of bitter apricot kernels and their hydrocyanic acid levels (1175 +/- 63.63 mg/kg).
